@RequestMapping("/a") <- handler mapping
CustomerController ‡∂ë‡∂ö "/a" URL path ‡∂ë‡∂ö‡∂ß map ‡∂ö‡∂ª‡∂∫‡∑í.

@GetMapping | @PostMapping | @PutMapping | @DeleteMapping
http method ‡∂ë‡∂ö ‡∂ö‡∑í‡∂∫‡∂±‡∑ä‡∂± Use ‡∂ö‡∂ª‡∂∫‡∑í. (Handler method ‡∂ã‡∂©‡∑í‡∂±‡∑ä ‡∂Ø‡∑è‡∂± annotations)


üîπ @RestController ‚Üí Marks this class as a REST API controller. It tells Spring Boot that this class will handle HTTP requests and return responses.
üîπ @RequestMapping("api/v1/customer") ‚Üí Defines the base URL (/api/v1/customer) for all endpoints inside this class.
üîπ @Autowired ‚Üí Injects the CustomerSevice class into this controller so that we can call service methods.

‚úîÔ∏è @DeleteMapping("delete/{id}") ‚Üí Handles DELETE requests at /api/v1/customer/delete/{id}.
‚úîÔ∏è @PathVariable int id ‚Üí Extracts the customer ID from the URL.
‚úîÔ∏è Calls deleteCustomer(id) in CustomerSevice, deleting the customer with the given ID.

